mode: agent
---
Explain the following in SIG: ${input:target:Which controller, API, or set of endpoints? e.g. "OrderController" or "OrderController's /orders/{id} and /orders/{id}/cancel endpoints"}

Follow Standing instruction A from copilot-instructions.md exactly:
1. Controller & endpoint summary (method, path, request/response)
2. Business logic in plain terms
3. Every SCS-Commons submodule this code actually calls into — trace it
   from real imports/dependency injection/method calls, don't guess.
   For each submodule: what it does generally, and how this specific
   endpoint uses it.
4. If a section doesn't apply (e.g. no SCS-Commons usage), say so
   explicitly instead of skipping it silently.

Cite file paths for every claim.
