## Day-to-day usage — both directions

**"Which SCS-Commons modules does this API use?"**
```
/explain-api OrderController
```

**"Who's using this module, and what does it need?"**
```
/explain-module-usage audit-logging
```

Because both standing instructions live in `copilot-instructions.md`
(always-on), even a plain question like *"what does the audit-logging
module need to work?"* — without using the slash command — should still
trigger the full structured answer. The prompt files are just consistent
shortcuts.

**Sanity check after setup:** ask one question each direction, then check
the References panel on the reply to confirm `copilot-instructions.md`
is listed as a loaded reference.
